slog
------------------------------------------
SLog is simple and thread safe logging library for C/C++. Software is written
for educational purposes and is distributed in the hope that it will be useful
for anyone interested in this field.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libslog-devel-1.8.22-1bl1
  libslog1-1.8.22-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  ninja-1.11.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/kala13x/slog

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/kala13x/slog/archive/refs/tags/1.8.22.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack slog-1.8.22-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./slog-1.8.22-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/slog-1.8.22-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/slog-1.8.22-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libslog1-1.8.22-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libslog-devel-1.8.22-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(slog)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/slog.README
  /usr/share/doc/slog/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/slog/README.md

(libslog1)
  /usr/bin/cygslog-1.dll

(libslog-devel)
  /usr/include/slog.h
  /usr/lib/libslog.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/slog.pc

------------------

Port Notes:

